headline: PayPal Stock Surges on OpenAI Partnership. Oh Yeah, It Reported Earnings, Declares Dividend, Too.
summary: PayPal Holdings  topped Wall Street’s expectations for earnings and revenue in the third quarter and raised its guidance for the year, citing “broad-based profitable growth” across its various lines of business.  Shares of PayPal rose 12% to $78.38, on pace for its largest same-day percentage increase since July 27, 2022, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  PayPal’s latest results broadly beat projections.

headline: Block (SQ) Valuation: Exploring Potential Upside as Investor Interest Builds
summary: Block (NYSE:XYZ) shares have quietly drifted higher over the past month, not due to headline-grabbing developments but because of steady investor interest. The stock is up 9% in that span, reflecting a broader curiosity about its valuation. See our latest analysis for Block. Block’s recent 1-month share price return of 8.8% has attracted attention, especially after a subdued start to the year. The stock’s 1-year total shareholder return sits at 9.5%, which hints at budding investor optimism...

headline: 1 Cash-Heavy Stock with Exciting Potential and 2 We Question
summary: Companies with more cash than debt can be financially resilient, but that doesn’t mean they’re all strong investments. Some lack leverage because they struggle to grow or generate consistent profits, making them unattractive borrowers.
